3 Compute the Jeffreys prior for the parameter . The Jeffreys prior in the univariate case is defined as

J()I()J()I()
with
I()=E[d2logp(y|)d2]I()=E[d2logp(y|)d2]
 Is it a proper distribution? Compute the posterior distribution.

Sol The Jeffreys prior is
J()1/2J()1/2

4-R Simulate three random samples of size 20, 100 and 1000 from a Poisson distribution with parameter =.5=.5.

Assume a prior gamma distribution for the parameter with the following four sets of hyperparameters:

  • 1=11=.51=11=.5
  • 2=12=22=12=2
  • 3=13=103=13=10
  • 4=24=24=24=2
  1. Plot the four prior distributions on the same graph, then add the Jeffreys prior.
set.seed(123)

y20   <- rpois(20, .5)
y100  <- rpois(100, .5)
y1000 <- rpois(1000, .5)

a <- c(1, 1, 1, 2, .5)
b <- c(.5, 2, 10, 2, 0)

priordist <- function(theta, k){
    if(k==5){return(1/sqrt(theta))}
    return(dgamma(theta, a[k], b[k]))
}

xl <- c(0,3)
yl <- c(0,3)

plot(c(),c(),xlim=xl,ylim=yl,main="Prior",xlab="",ylab="")
for(k in 1:5) curve(priordist(x,k), add=T, col=k)
legend(2.5, 2.5,
       legend=c("Gamma1", "Gamma2",
                "Gamma3", "Gamma4",
                "Jeffreys'"),
       col=c(1:5), lty=1, cex=0.8)

  1. For each simulated dataset, plot on the same graph the five posterior distributions.
postdist <- function(theta,y,k){
  return(dgamma(theta,a[k]+sum(y),b[k]+length(y)))
}

plot(c(),c(),xlim=xl,ylim=yl,main="n=20",xlab="",ylab="")
for(k in 1:5) curve(postdist(x,y20,k), add=T, col=k)

plot(c(),c(),xlim=xl,ylim=yl,main="n=100",xlab="",ylab="")
for(k in 1:5) curve(postdist(x,y100,k), add=T, col=k)

plot(c(),c(),xlim=xl,ylim=yl,main="n=1000",xlab="",ylab="")
for(k in 1:5) curve(postdist(x,y1000,k), add=T, col=k)

  2. Construct the 95% credible intervals, equi-tails and highest posterior density (HPD), for the three datasets using the Jeffreys prior.

qgamma(c(.025,.975),-.5+sum(y20),20)
## [1] 0.2570724 0.8869719
qgamma(c(.025,.975),-.5+sum(y100),100)
## [1] 0.3582076 0.6307072
qgamma(c(.025,.975),-.5+sum(y1000),1000)
## [1] 0.4365814 0.5223127
hpd<-function(y,p){
dy<-density(y)
md<-dy$x[dy$y==max(dy$y)]
py<-dy$y/sum(dy$y)
pys<--sort(-py)
ct<-min(pys[cumsum(pys)< p])
list(hpdr=range(dy$x[py>=ct]),mode=md)
}
